                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Elastic",
                "scattering of 6Li+28Si at near-barrier energies.",
                "Details of measurement method"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "2GRCATH"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 180-ug/cm2-thick, self-supported natural silicon",
                "target, tilted by +/- 40 degree (depending on the",
                "detector position). A liquid-nitrogen cold trap close",
                "to the target holder reduced the target contamination",
                "on carbon to minimum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "14-SI-28(3-LI-6,EL)14-SI-28,,DA",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "14-SI-28(3-LI-6,EL)14-SI-28,,DA",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "14-SI-28(3-LI-6,EL)14-SI-28",
                        "target": "14-SI-28",
                        "projectile": "3-LI-6",
                        "process": "EL",
                        "product": "14-SI-28",
                        "quantity": ",DA",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The scattering at",
                "+/- 15 degree, concerning the present bombarding",
                "energies, can be considered as being pure Rutherford."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The dE silicon detector was 10 um thick,",
                "while the E detector was 300 um thick measuring the",
                "forward-angle scattering. The alpha group was well",
                "discriminated in the forward detectors with the",
                "dE-E technique."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A thin, 20- or 25-um - thick silicon",
                "detector measuring the backward scattering. The",
                "choice of the thickness of the backward detector was",
                "such as to allow light particles, like alphas from",
                "breakup transfer and other contaminant reactions",
                " (6Li+12C), to go through while Li particles stop in",
                "the detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " two monitor Si(Li) detectors, 300 um thick, at",
                "15.degr., fixed on a top table concentric to the",
                "bottom rotating one and measuring the elastic",
                "scattering of lithium."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 6Li+ beam. Beam currents were of the order of",
                "30 nA."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The alpha group was well discriminated in the",
                "forward detectors with the dE-E technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
